sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser
    participant API as API Server (Hono + Better Auth)
    participant Entra as Azure Entra ID (OIDC)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL (NOVA DB)
    participant Redis

    Note over Browser, Redis: Azure Entra ID OIDC Login Flow

    Browser->>API: GET /auth/sso/entra
    API->>API: Generate state + PKCE code_verifier
    API->>Redis: Store state + code_verifier (TTL 10 min)
    API-->>Browser: 302 Redirect to Entra /authorize

    Browser->>Entra: GET /authorize (client_id, redirect_uri, response_type=code, scope=openid profile email, state, code_challenge)
    Entra-->>Browser: Login page (credentials / MFA)

    Browser->>Entra: Submit credentials
    Entra-->>Browser: 302 Redirect to /auth/callback/entra?code=X&state=Y

    Browser->>API: GET /auth/callback/entra?code=X&state=Y

    API->>Redis: Retrieve + validate state + code_verifier
    Redis-->>API: Stored state + code_verifier

    API->>Entra: POST /token (code, code_verifier, client_secret)
    Entra-->>API: id_token + access_token + refresh_token

    API->>API: Validate id_token signature via JWKS
    API->>API: Extract claims (sub, email, name, oid)

    alt User exists in DB
        API->>DB: SELECT user WHERE entra_oid = claims.sub
        DB-->>API: Existing user record
    else New user (first login)
        API->>DB: INSERT user (email, name, entra_oid)
        API->>DB: INSERT org_member (default org, role: member)
        DB-->>API: New user record
    end

    API->>DB: INSERT session (user_id, expires_at)
    DB-->>API: Session record

    API->>Redis: Cache session (TTL matches expiry)

    API-->>Browser: 302 Redirect to /app + Set-Cookie: session_token (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax)

    Note over Browser, Redis: Subsequent API Requests

    Browser->>API: GET /api/conversations (Cookie: session_token)
    API->>Redis: Lookup session (cache hit)
    Redis-->>API: Session + user context
    API->>API: Inject tenant context (org_id, role)
    API-->>Browser: 200 OK (data)

    Note over Browser, Redis: Session Refresh

    Browser->>API: GET /auth/session
    API->>API: Check session expiry
    alt Session near expiry
        API->>DB: UPDATE session (extend expires_at)
        API->>Redis: Update cached session
        API-->>Browser: 200 OK (refreshed session)
    else Session valid
        API-->>Browser: 200 OK (current session)
    end
